Package com.cafean.client.ui.beans

Class PropertySet

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.client.ui.beans.PropertySet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ComponentListener, java.beans.PropertyChangeListener, java.util.EventListener
    public class PropertySet
extends java.lang.Object
implements ComponentListener, java.beans.PropertyChangeListener
    PropertySet is a synchronized container of a set of Java Beans with accessors and filters for their properties.

    This class allows its clients to filter thier queries on two concepts:
    The first is the PropertyController interface's DISABLED, REQUIRED and OPTIONAL enumerations.
    The second is a named grouping called an Attribute Group.

    For a bean to support Attribute Groups it simply implements public static String getAttributeGroup( String property ), which, given a property name, will return the name of the Attribute Group that the given property is part of.

    With this capability, the PropertySets clients can filter out all but the groupings theyre designated to display.

    See Also:
    PropertySetPanel, GroupPanel, PropertyPanel

      • setComponentEventsEnabled

        public void setComponentEventsEnabled​(boolean enabled)
        This method is used to enable/disable the component changed events delivered to this property set's target components when an editor finishes (i.e. fires a PropertyChangeEvent).

        When set to true (the default) AbstractComponent.fireComponentChanged() will be called. When set to false it will not.

        Parameters:
        enabled - if true the events will be fired; if false they will not
